Introduction
❑ This presentation serves as our 3-part marketing-centric case study as part of the Consulting
and Analytics Club, IIT Guwahati.
❑ The spotlight will be on myGate, a Bangalore-based startup offering security solutions
through an app-based interface. Easing the lives of millions of users, it has quickly risen from
employing an small ﬂagship solution in 2016, to being placed in formidable line-ups like
“India’s Coolest/Most Innovative Startups”.
❑ It is also worth mentioning that Shreyans Daga, one of the co-founders and the current CTO
of myGate, was an alumnus of IIT Guwahati, batch of 2004. Thus, we feel immense pride in
retracing the journey Mr. Daga and his colleagues would have undertaken before myGate’s
launch in 2016, blazing a path forward and inspiring us, being in the same shoes he was, 20
years ago.

BIO:
Palmgrove Avenue is a small residential society in the industrial region of the city. Most of
the residents’ concerns are handled by the close-knit Executive Body, and security contracts
are given out to low-cost security agencies.

75 x 150 ≈ 11,250 societies all over India.
